        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 3:27PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 326 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles west of Saguache, or 45 miles northwest of Alamosa, moving
southeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Saguache.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
